<paragraph blockId="32.[151,1437,188,575]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,348,260,287]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Occurrence:</emphasis>
North Atlantic, Northeast American coast, north of Cape Hatteras to 
<collectingCountry box="[1117,1234,261,287]" name="Greenland" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Greenland</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[1287,1372,261,287]" name="Iceland" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Iceland</collectingCountry>
, eastwards to Scandinavia, southwards to the 
<collectingCountry box="[620,796,297,323]" name="Western Sahara" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Western Sahara</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Paterson" box="[813,997,296,323]" firstAuthor="Paterson" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" pagination="1 - 162" refId="ref195005" refString="Paterson, G. L. J. (1985) The deep-sea Ophiuroidea of the North Atlantic Ocean. Bulletin of the British Museum (Natural History), Zoology Series, 49 (1), 1 - 162." type="journal article" year="1985">Paterson (1985)</bibRefCitation>
, including the Azores (
<bibRefCitation author="Koehler" box="[1263,1424,297,323]" firstAuthor="Koehler" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" pagination="1 - 317" refId="ref185837" refString="Koehler, R. (1909) Echinodermes provenant des campagnes du yacht Princesse-Alice (Asteries, Ophiures, Echinides et Crinoides). Resultats des campagnes scientifiques accomplies sur son yacht par Albert Ier Prince Souverain de Monaco, 34, 1 - 317." type="journal article" year="1909">Koehler 1909</bibRefCitation>
), Madeira (
<bibRefCitation author="Jesus &amp; Abreu" box="[259,508,333,359]" firstAuthor="Jesus" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" pagination="59 - 69" refId="ref184817" refString="Jesus, D. &amp; Abreu, A. D. (1998) Contribution to the knowledge of the soft bottom echinoderms of Madeira Island. Boletim do Museu Municipal do Funchal (Historia Natural), 50 (286), 59 - 69., 4 figs." type="book chapter" year="1998">Jesus &amp; Abreu (1998)</bibRefCitation>
, Canaries (
<bibRefCitation author="Madsen" box="[632,790,333,359]" firstAuthor="Madsen" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" pagination="151 - 243" refId="ref189192" refString="Madsen, F. J. (1970) West African Ophiuroids. Atlantidae Report, 11, 151 - 243." type="journal article" year="1970">Madsen 1970</bibRefCitation>
), and the 
<taxonomicName authority="Seamount (A. H. Clark 1949)" authorityName="Seamount (A. H. Clark" authorityYear="1949" box="[896,1319,333,359]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Atlantis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
Atlantis Seamount (A.H. 
<bibRefCitation author="Clark" box="[1182,1311,333,359]" firstAuthor="Clark" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" pagination="371 - 377" refId="ref176404" refString="Clark, A. H. (1949) Echinoderms from the mid-Atlantic dredged by lhe Atlantis in the summer of 1948. Journal of the Washington Academy of Sciences, 39, 371 - 377." type="journal article" year="1949">Clark 1949</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="32.[151,1437,188,575]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,282,369,395]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Depth:</emphasis>
35– 
<quantity box="[330,424,368,395]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" unit="m" value="3.5">3,500 m</quantity>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Mortensen" box="[439,658,369,395]" firstAuthor="Mortensen" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" refId="ref192564" refString="Mortensen, T. (1927 a) Handbook of the echinoderms of the British Isles. Oxford University Press, viii + 471 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 6841" type="book" year="1927" yearSuffix="a">Mortensen (1927a)</bibRefCitation>
, an upper bathyal species that may occur in shallow waters at higher latitudes, such as the Norwegian Sea (
<bibRefCitation author="Gage" box="[576,767,405,431]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Gage" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" pagination="263 - 308" refId="ref181395" refString="Gage, J. D., Billett, D. S. M., Jensen, M. &amp; Tyler, P. A. (1983) Echinoderms of the Rockall Trough and adjacent areas. I. Crinoidea, Asteroidea and Ophiuroidea. Bulletin of the British Museum (Natural History), Zoology, 45, 263 - 308. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. part. 28002" type="journal article" year="1983">
Gage 
<emphasis box="[644,693,405,431]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">et al</emphasis>
. 1983
</bibRefCitation>
); 
<collectionCode box="[786,848,405,431]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">AZO</collectionCode>
: 
<quantity box="[858,929,405,431]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.8" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" unit="m" value="880.0">880 m</quantity>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Koehler" box="[943,1102,405,431]" firstAuthor="Koehler" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" pagination="1 - 317" refId="ref185837" refString="Koehler, R. (1909) Echinodermes provenant des campagnes du yacht Princesse-Alice (Asteries, Ophiures, Echinides et Crinoides). Resultats des campagnes scientifiques accomplies sur son yacht par Albert Ier Prince Souverain de Monaco, 34, 1 - 317." type="journal article" year="1909">Koehler 1909</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="32.[151,1437,188,575]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,300,440,467]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Habitat:</emphasis>
rock, coral, mud to gravel and detritic substrates (
<bibRefCitation author="Farran" box="[863,1004,441,467]" firstAuthor="Farran" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" pagination="1 - 66" refId="ref180217" refString="Farran, G. P. (1913) The deep-water Asteroidea, Ophiuroidea and Echinoidea of the West Coast of Ireland. Department of Agriculture and technical instruction for Ireland, fisheries branch, scientific investigations, 6, 1 - 66. [1912]" type="journal article" year="1913">Farran 1913</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Cherbonnier" box="[1016,1222,441,467]" firstAuthor="Cherbonnier" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" pagination="343 - 361" refId="ref175887" refString="Cherbonnier, G. (1969) Echinodermes recoltes par la &quot; Thalassa &quot; au large de cotes d'espagne et du Golfe de Gascogne (3 - 12 AOUT 1967). Bulletin Museum National Histoire Naturelle Paris, Serie 2, 41 (1), 343 - 361." type="journal article" year="1969">Cherbonnier 1969</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Cherbonnier" box="[1233,1293,441,467]" firstAuthor="Cherbonnier" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" pagination="1266 - 1277" refId="ref175938" refString="Cherbonnier, G. (1970) Echinodermes recoltes par la &quot; Thalassa &quot; au large de cotes d'espagne et du Golfe de Gascogne (18 - 25 AOUT 1968). Bulletin Museum National Histoire Naturelle, Paris, 2 ª Serie, 41 (5), 1266 - 1277." type="journal article" year="1970">1970</bibRefCitation>
); it can form dense beds (
<bibRefCitation author="Metaxas &amp; Giffin" box="[288,556,477,503]" firstAuthor="Metaxas" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" pagination="1307 - 1317" refId="ref190461" refString="Metaxas, A. &amp; Giffin, B. (2004) Dense beds of the ophiuroid Ophiacantha abyssicola on the continental slope off Nova Scotia, Canada. Deep-Sea Research I, 51, 1307 - 1317. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. dsr. 2004.06.001" type="journal article" year="2004">Metaxas &amp; Giffin 2004</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="32.[151,1437,188,575]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,317,513,539]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Remarks:</emphasis>
the record of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sars" authorityYear="1872" box="[471,742,513,539]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiacanthidae" genus="Ophiacantha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="abyssicola">
<emphasis box="[471,742,513,539]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Ophiacantha abyssicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the 
<collectingRegion box="[815,894,513,539]" country="Portugal" name="Acores" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Azores</collectingRegion>
is based on a single small specimen collected by 
<emphasis box="[151,325,549,575]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Princesse Alice</emphasis>
(sta 837: 
<geoCoordinate box="[435,534,548,575]" degrees="37" direction="north" minutes="55" orientation="latitude" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" precision="925" value="37.916668">37°55’N</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate box="[546,690,548,575]" degrees="25" direction="west" minutes="24" orientation="longitude" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" precision="15" seconds="15" value="-25.404167">25°24’15”W</geoCoordinate>
, 
<quantity box="[701,773,549,575]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.8" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" unit="m" value="880.0">880 m</quantity>
) and identified by 
<bibRefCitation author="Koehler" box="[985,1159,549,575]" firstAuthor="Koehler" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" pagination="1 - 317" refId="ref185837" refString="Koehler, R. (1909) Echinodermes provenant des campagnes du yacht Princesse-Alice (Asteries, Ophiures, Echinides et Crinoides). Resultats des campagnes scientifiques accomplies sur son yacht par Albert Ier Prince Souverain de Monaco, 34, 1 - 317." type="journal article" year="1909">Koehler (1909)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
